Headlines.Author: John Kell
Headlines.Headline: EOG Resources, Newfield Terminate Marcellus Shale Sale Pact

PARAGRAPH.#text: DOW JONES NEWSWIRES EOG Resources Inc. EOG and Newfield Exploration Co. NFX said they have mutually agreed to terminate an agreement announced last month regarding EOG's planned sale of 50,000 acres of natural-gas rich land in Pennsylvania's Marcellus Shale. The sale was expected to total $405 million and, at the time, it was expected the deal would close by the end of the year. The acreage represented less than 0.5% of EOG's North American production, and EOG was expected to retain 170,000 net acres in the Marcellus shale, a tight rock formation spanning several northeastern states, if the sale were to occur.

PARAGRAPH.#text:
NEW YORK (CBS.MW) -- U.S. shares picked up significant steam Tuesday, with
    investors displaying a hearty appetite for tech issues in particular, as a two-day Federal
    Open Market Committee meeting commenced Tuesday. Buyers stepped in for a second straight
    session to scoop up shares as they awaited the outcome of the Fed gathering, which is
    widely anticipated to produce a 25-basis-point rise in short-term rates Wednesday. The
    Nasdaq ended higher on the days the Fed hiked interest rates last year -- June 30, Aug. 24
    and Nov. 16 -- while the Dow posted gains on only two of those days.
